h radiative cores, the less X-ray luminous they\nbecome. The decay of coronal X-ray emission from young early K to late G-type\nPMS stars, the progenitors of main sequence A-type stars, is consistent with\nthe dearth of X-ray detections of the latter.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 28 Jan 2016 21:15:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-02-17"}
